      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite covering hemolysis-relevant flow regimes; traceability from requirements to test cases required at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM 9) is version-controlled and has a documented regression suite, but the suite does not cover rotating-frame hemolysis transport. Achieved level 2 reflects basic version control without domain-specific SQA coverage."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification for all transport equations including hemolysis scalar transport; method of manufactured solutions applied to rotating-frame formulation.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests performed for momentum equations only; hemolysis scalar transport equation not verified via MMS. Achieved level 2 because core flow solver verification exists but hemolysis-specific verification is absent."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes with GCI < 5% on NIH at all operating points; spatial and temporal discretization errors reported separately.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation performed; GCI on NIH ranges from 8–14% across operating points, exceeding the 5% threshold. Temporal discretization error estimated but not separated from spatial error in the reported GCI."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate all five clinical flow-speed combinations; fluid temperature, hematocrit, and anticoagulant protocol fully documented and matched to simulation inputs.",
      "rationale": "Three of five operating points replicated in bench testing; hematocrit documented at 33% but temperature control ±2°C introduces viscosity uncertainty not propagated into the hemolysis model. Achieved level 3 reflects partial condition matching."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel, NRMSE) with uncertainty bands on both simulation and experiment; statistical equivalence test at 95% confidence required for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Relative error computed but no formal statistical equivalence test performed. Experimental uncertainty quantified only for two of three tested operating points. Achieved level 2 because comparison is qualitative trend-matching without statistical rigor."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoI must be NIH or equivalent absolute hemolysis measure directly linked to clinical acceptance threshold; surrogate QoIs (e.g., shear stress only) insufficient at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "NIH used as primary validation QoI, directly matching the clinical threshold metric. However, the hemolysis power-law exponents were calibrated on a different pump geometry, introducing model-form relevance uncertainty. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must span the full clinical operating envelope (all 5 flow-speed combinations) with the actual device geometry and blood analogue fluid at physiological hematocrit.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic pump geometry (matching COU device) but only 3 of 5 operating points tested. Blood analogue (PDMS-water) used rather than ovine blood, reducing physiological relevance. Achieved level 3."
    },
