      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity analysis across at least two hemolysis power-law formulations (e.g., Giersiepen-Wurzinger and Taskin models); model-form uncertainty contribution to NIH quantified and included in total uncertainty budget.",
      "rationale": "Single hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) used throughout. No model-form sensitivity study performed. Model-form uncertainty is the dominant unquantified source at MRL 5. Achieved level 2 reflects literature acknowledgment without local quantification."
    },
